Description: Centre, representation of the Roman God of good fortune, 'Bonus Eventus'. (obverse)

Centre, depiction of the two frigates that carried Napoleon and his suite back from Egypt, in full sail; background right, two ships just visible on the horizon, representitive of the English ships that were sighted when Napoleon made for the French coast from Corsica; upper right, a star. (reverse)
Producer name: Die Engraved or Modelled for Reducing Machine: André Galle
